1
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:44,800
=Love Story in the 1970s=

2
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:47,940
=Episode 4=

3
00:02:02,740 --> 00:02:03,540
Fang Muyang.

4
00:02:04,650 --> 00:02:06,000
Sometimes, I think

5
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:07,530
you must've gone mad

6
00:02:07,530 --> 00:02:09,020
when you joined the production team.

7
00:02:10,090 --> 00:02:10,660
Why?

8
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:12,460
If you're not mad,

9
00:02:12,460 --> 00:02:15,420
why would you let Ling Yi
take your place in university?

10
00:02:18,626 --> 00:02:20,071
I guess it makes sense, though.

11
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:21,210
She's your girlfriend.

12
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,250
It's only natural.

13
00:02:23,930 --> 00:02:24,890
But if it were me,

14
00:02:24,890 --> 00:02:25,860
I wouldn't do that.

15
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,982
No worries. You can take my place.

16
00:02:33,450 --> 00:02:34,170
You think

17
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:35,670
university slots

18
00:02:35,670 --> 00:02:37,090
are as common as corn kernels,

19
00:02:37,137 --> 00:02:38,760
and you can pick them off the ground?

20
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:42,410
Still, why were you chosen, though?

21
00:02:43,137 --> 00:02:44,440
Is there some sort of trick?

22
00:02:48,450 --> 00:02:49,648
Are you okay?

23
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:51,500
That hurts.

24
00:02:52,026 --> 00:02:53,537
By the way, what's your name?

25
00:02:53,810 --> 00:02:54,590
I'm Ling Yi.

26
00:02:54,970 --> 00:02:56,000
And you?

27
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:57,130
I'm Ye Feng.

28
00:02:58,090 --> 00:02:59,360
Are you from this school?

29
00:02:59,530 --> 00:02:59,900
Yes.

30
00:03:00,140 --> 00:03:01,170
You remember Ling Yi?

31
00:03:02,426 --> 00:03:03,970
She visited me in the hospital.

32
00:03:06,530 --> 00:03:07,110
Ling Yi!

33
00:03:12,370 --> 00:03:13,780
Fei Ni, what a coincidence.

34
00:03:14,250 --> 00:03:16,070
You're here to watch
our basketball match?

35
00:03:16,850 --> 00:03:17,900
You know each other?

36
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:19,900
Of course.

37
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:22,970
Fei Ni works in
Jiangcheng No. 1 Textile Factory,

38
00:03:22,970 --> 00:03:24,870
and I'm in the factory's
basketball team.

39
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:32,810
And this is?

40
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:37,810
He's Fang Muyang,

41
00:03:37,893 --> 00:03:39,737
the hero who saved lives
in the thunderstorm.

42
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,090
Hello, Fang Muyang.

43
00:03:42,370 --> 00:03:43,150
I'm Ye Feng.

44
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:45,910
I'm the captain of Jiangcheng No. 1
Textile Factory's basketball team.

45
00:03:47,590 --> 00:03:48,150
Hello.

46
00:03:48,570 --> 00:03:49,570
I'm Fang Muyang.

47
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:51,490
You look tall

48
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:52,500
and strong.

49
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:54,137
You'd be a great addition to our team.

50
00:03:54,170 --> 00:03:54,900
Want to join?

51
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:55,650
Ye Feng.

52
00:03:55,970 --> 00:03:57,200
Fei Ni is here for me.

53
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,150
You can go now.

54
00:03:58,250 --> 00:04:00,115
Fei Ni will take me
to the infirmary.

55
00:04:01,210 --> 00:04:01,880
No worries.

56
00:04:02,230 --> 00:04:03,880
I'm free, so let's go together.

57
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:09,690
Ye Feng, Ling Yi and I have
something private to discuss.

58
00:04:11,970 --> 00:04:12,460
Fair enough.

59
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:13,190
Go ahead.

60
00:04:13,337 --> 00:04:15,315
The boys are waiting for me
at the court, anyway.

61
00:04:15,430 --> 00:04:16,140
I'm off.

62
00:04:16,470 --> 00:04:16,840
Bye.

63
00:04:17,271 --> 00:04:18,050
Consider my offer.

64
00:04:22,770 --> 00:04:24,360
Is your hand okay?

65
00:04:28,770 --> 00:04:29,440
I'm okay.

66
00:04:30,210 --> 00:04:32,010
So, let's talk.

67
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:42,660
The way he draws

68
00:04:42,660 --> 00:04:44,090
still looks the same.

69
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:46,693
He doesn't look like
he's lost his memories.

70
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:51,540
He hasn't remembered the past,

71
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:54,310
but he's learned a lot of life skills.

72
00:04:54,830 --> 00:04:56,030
In principle,

73
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:58,640
other than forgetting the past,

74
00:04:58,740 --> 00:04:59,860
he's totally normal.

75
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,570
Not exactly.

76
00:05:03,740 --> 00:05:05,240
The way he looks at me

77
00:05:05,830 --> 00:05:06,890
feels so distant.

78
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:09,310
If you can visit him more often,

79
00:05:09,660 --> 00:05:10,980
perhaps he'd get better.

80
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:15,890
Fei Ni.

81
00:05:16,630 --> 00:05:18,500
I know you look down on me.

82
00:05:19,071 --> 00:05:20,890
But you don't know
what I've been through.

83
00:05:20,890 --> 00:05:22,210
You have no right to lecture me.

84
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:24,300
I'm not looking down on you.

85
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:27,680
I think you have the right
to pursue your own happiness.

86
00:05:27,770 --> 00:05:29,210
But this isn't the time

87
00:05:29,210 --> 00:05:30,610
to leave Fang Muyang alone.

88
00:05:30,890 --> 00:05:32,570
What do you want me to do?

89
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:34,450
I'm not a doctor.

90
00:05:34,450 --> 00:05:35,660
I can't cure him.

91
00:05:35,660 --> 00:05:37,070
But you're his girlfriend.

92
00:05:37,226 --> 00:05:38,510
You've been working together,

93
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:40,330
and have been dating for so many years.

94
00:05:40,330 --> 00:05:41,310
You know him best.

95
00:05:41,690 --> 00:05:42,960
Dr. Liang also said

96
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:44,860
that if you can help him
recall the past,

97
00:05:44,860 --> 00:05:46,620
it can help him recover his memory.

98
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:48,490
That's why I'm here

99
00:05:48,670 --> 00:05:50,050
to ask you to help him.

100
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:51,026
I'm not his girlfriend.

101
00:05:51,170 --> 00:05:52,110
I can't help him.

102
00:05:54,004 --> 00:05:55,840
Those words came from your own mouth.

103
00:06:04,382 --> 00:06:05,248
Fei Ni.

104
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:07,920
You're noble and selfless.

105
00:06:08,660 --> 00:06:10,540
You can sacrifice yourself
to take care of him.

106
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:11,515
That's your own choice.

107
00:06:11,515 --> 00:06:12,915
You can't demand me to do the same.

108
00:06:13,370 --> 00:06:14,240
Let me repeat this.

109
00:06:14,690 --> 00:06:15,770
I'm not his girlfriend.

110
00:06:16,340 --> 00:06:17,860
Don't talk to me again.

111
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:01,540
What is this place?

112
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:03,620
It's pretty.

113
00:07:06,010 --> 00:07:06,850
Pretty, right?

114
00:07:07,210 --> 00:07:07,860
Yeah.

115
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:10,670
My brother and I
often came here to play as kids.

116
00:07:11,715 --> 00:07:13,620
I still come here when I feel down.

117
00:07:23,404 --> 00:07:24,370
What are you doing?

118
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:26,940
Back in the hospital,

119
00:07:26,940 --> 00:07:28,560
the girl from the next room
cheers up

120
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:29,480
when her dad does this.

121
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:32,740
Don't you try that on me.

122
00:07:38,540 --> 00:07:39,210
Fang Muyang.

123
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:42,750
If you can never remember

124
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:43,770
the past,

125
00:07:44,210 --> 00:07:45,190
what should we do?

126
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:47,810
The past?

127
00:07:49,060 --> 00:07:49,700
Is it important?

128
00:07:50,737 --> 00:07:52,915
I think there's nothing wrong
with the present.

129
00:07:53,100 --> 00:07:54,520
If I can't remember the past,

130
00:07:55,093 --> 00:07:56,450
it means it's not that important.

131
00:07:57,540 --> 00:07:58,700
If I forget my old friends,

132
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:00,890
I'll just make new ones.

133
00:08:02,340 --> 00:08:03,600
Actually, I don't understand

134
00:08:04,540 --> 00:08:05,110
why everyone

135
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:06,570
wants me to remember the past.

136
00:08:08,210 --> 00:08:09,690
Even if I can't remember,

137
00:08:10,330 --> 00:08:11,330
I'm still me.

138
00:08:12,770 --> 00:08:14,300
I won't become someone else.

139
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:20,450
Don't you feel like
there's a burden on your chest?

140
00:08:21,180 --> 00:08:22,270
A little, at first.

141
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:23,710
But not anymore.

142
00:08:24,860 --> 00:08:25,770
Because you're around.

143
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:33,937
Do you remember where you used to live?

144
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:39,680
Kangnan Road.

145
00:08:39,970 --> 00:08:41,020
When we were young,

146
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:42,460
you brought us to your house.

147
00:08:48,810 --> 00:08:49,380
Come on.

148
00:08:57,900 --> 00:09:03,180
(44 Kangnan Road)

149
00:09:23,780 --> 00:09:24,730
Do you remember?

150
00:09:25,970 --> 00:09:26,970
You used to live here.

151
00:09:28,210 --> 00:09:29,550
Can you remember anything?

152
00:09:39,490 --> 00:09:42,520
This place probably looks different

153
00:09:42,782 --> 00:09:43,960
from when you were around.

154
00:09:44,570 --> 00:09:45,210
It's okay.

155
00:09:46,090 --> 00:09:47,020
Let's look around.

156
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:48,180
Come on.

157
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:02,600
Go, brother!

158
00:10:03,570 --> 00:10:04,880
Go, brother!

159
00:10:07,730 --> 00:10:09,760
Go, brother!

160
00:10:13,248 --> 00:10:14,600
(You're climbing trees again?)

161
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:16,100
(Get down!)

162
00:10:18,940 --> 00:10:19,570
Yang!

163
00:10:23,210 --> 00:10:25,210
Yang, you're climbing trees again?

164
00:10:25,315 --> 00:10:27,070
You'll be squealing in pain
when you fall!

165
00:10:27,380 --> 00:10:28,290
Get down!

166
00:10:28,570 --> 00:10:30,690
(I bought ice cream today.)

167
00:10:31,370 --> 00:10:34,400
(- Happy birthday to you...)
(- Get down!)

168
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:36,590
(I bought ice cream today.)

169
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:38,090
Hao!

170
00:10:38,090 --> 00:10:39,380
Why are you climbing trees again?

171
00:10:39,420 --> 00:10:40,180
Get down!

172
00:10:43,610 --> 00:10:44,380
Why you...

173
00:10:44,380 --> 00:10:45,550
You naughty boy!

174
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:47,090
If not for him,

175
00:10:47,090 --> 00:10:48,220
you'd have broken your leg!

176
00:10:48,810 --> 00:10:49,970
Thank you, comrade.

177
00:10:49,970 --> 00:10:50,560
Thank you.

178
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:52,180
- You're welcome.
- Go home!

179
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:52,980
Go!

180
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,070
I'll tell your father

181
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:55,200
what you've been up to.

182
00:10:55,380 --> 00:10:57,100
If you climb trees again,

183
00:10:57,271 --> 00:10:58,300
I'll beat your legs up!

184
00:11:01,630 --> 00:11:03,330
You may have lost your memories,

185
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:05,490
but your heroic spirit is still there.

186
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:09,440
Fei Ni.

187
00:11:09,530 --> 00:11:09,990
Yes?

188
00:11:10,140 --> 00:11:10,810
Let's go.

189
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:13,430
Don't you want to go up?

190
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:14,850
I want some ice cream.

191
00:11:21,210 --> 00:11:21,740
Thank you.

192
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:22,690
You're welcome.

193
00:11:25,570 --> 00:11:26,970
You've been doing great today,

194
00:11:26,970 --> 00:11:28,626
so here's some ice cream as a reward.

195
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:34,560
That's not ice cream.

196
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:37,300
This is ice cream.

197
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,730
It's not.

198
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:39,650
What do you mean?

199
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:40,810
It is ice cream.

200
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,570
This is what ice cream looks like.

201
00:12:08,450 --> 00:12:09,180
Yours isn't.

202
00:12:13,070 --> 00:12:15,690
All you can think of is food, huh?

203
00:12:15,850 --> 00:12:17,640
I can't afford that expensive stuff.

204
00:12:17,671 --> 00:12:18,700
All I have is popsicles.

205
00:12:18,782 --> 00:12:19,770
Take it or leave it.

206
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:43,330
Yummy.

207
00:12:59,826 --> 00:13:01,330
I'll buy you ice cream next time.

208
00:13:06,660 --> 00:13:07,900
Say.

209
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:11,390
If you didn't tell anyone you're sick,

210
00:13:11,730 --> 00:13:12,830
who'd have thought you are?

211
00:13:26,820 --> 00:13:27,610
Fang Muyang.

212
00:13:29,060 --> 00:13:30,380
Can I ask for a favor?

213
00:13:36,660 --> 00:13:37,260
Ice cream.

214
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:52,380
(Saving Lives,
Serving Workers and Peasants)

215
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,090
Fang Muyang.

216
00:14:01,690 --> 00:14:03,010
I've written a short account

217
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:05,060
of your parents and sister.

218
00:14:05,270 --> 00:14:06,690
It's not complete, but it's enough.

219
00:14:06,690 --> 00:14:09,690
I also made some stories about your time

220
00:14:10,420 --> 00:14:11,420
in the production team.

221
00:14:11,420 --> 00:14:13,000
Ms. Xu wouldn't know, anyway.

222
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,170
I think we can get by.

223
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:16,610
Most importantly, you need to remember

224
00:14:17,780 --> 00:14:18,940
this part.

225
00:14:19,730 --> 00:14:22,800
"When I was saving them,
my mind was blank.

226
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:25,910
That's because to me,
saving lives is an instinct.

227
00:14:25,910 --> 00:14:27,400
It doesn't require preparation.

228
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,580
If I must think of something,

229
00:14:28,580 --> 00:14:32,020
the only conviction I had

230
00:14:32,020 --> 00:14:33,720
was to stay determined,

231
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:34,830
sacrifice myself

232
00:14:34,830 --> 00:14:37,530
to overcome hurdles and succeed."

233
00:14:41,940 --> 00:14:43,140
Are you listening?

234
00:14:44,648 --> 00:14:46,610
You want me to pretend
that I've recovered

235
00:14:47,210 --> 00:14:48,180
to deceive your superior?

236
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:50,090
You...

237
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:54,490
Don't say that.

238
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:57,750
I know it's bad.

239
00:14:58,430 --> 00:15:00,610
I've been struggling inside for a while,

240
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,570
and I've run out of options.

241
00:15:03,020 --> 00:15:04,020
After all,

242
00:15:04,020 --> 00:15:06,010
I've been taking care of you
for so many days,

243
00:15:06,730 --> 00:15:07,860
so help me, please.

244
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:12,510
If you can help me,

245
00:15:13,910 --> 00:15:15,730
I'll buy you ice cream.

246
00:15:21,671 --> 00:15:22,810
What kind of face is that?

247
00:15:22,810 --> 00:15:23,660
Is that

248
00:15:24,030 --> 00:15:26,070
a no, or you can't memorize that?

249
00:15:28,810 --> 00:15:30,520
Yeah, you're still ill.

250
00:15:30,870 --> 00:15:31,900
It's pretty tough.

251
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:33,050
I'll make it shorter.

252
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:39,390
"When I was saving them,
my mind was blank.

253
00:15:40,090 --> 00:15:42,300
That's because to me,
saving lives is an instinct.

254
00:15:42,648 --> 00:15:44,120
It doesn't require preparation.

255
00:15:45,604 --> 00:15:46,850
If I must think of something,

256
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:49,970
the only conviction I had

257
00:15:51,730 --> 00:15:53,030
was to stay determined,

258
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:54,470
sacrifice myself

259
00:15:54,970 --> 00:15:55,850
to overcome hurdles

260
00:15:56,450 --> 00:15:57,380
and succeed."

261
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,260
Fang Muyang.

262
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:03,360
You're amazing!

263
00:16:07,490 --> 00:16:08,210
Fei Ni.

264
00:16:10,420 --> 00:16:11,330
Buy me an ice cream.

265
00:16:13,060 --> 00:16:13,850
It's a deal!

266
00:16:16,730 --> 00:16:19,330
This is great news!

267
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:20,730
I heard from Fei Ni

268
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,940
that you've recovered your full memory?

269
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:24,260
This is great news!

270
00:16:24,260 --> 00:16:25,080
Hello, Ms. Xu.

271
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,100
I've made a full recovery.

272
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:28,560
You may rest assured.

273
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:30,180
Now that you've recovered,

274
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:31,940
you look much more energetic!

275
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:34,020
Feng Lin.

276
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,280
Pour some tea.

277
00:16:35,590 --> 00:16:36,560
Ms. Xu, have a seat.

278
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:37,300
Sit down.

279
00:16:51,450 --> 00:16:52,400
Fang Muyang.

280
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:56,570
Have you really remembered everything?

281
00:17:02,810 --> 00:17:03,260
Yes.

282
00:17:03,610 --> 00:17:05,200
He's remembered basically everything.

283
00:17:05,380 --> 00:17:07,530
But his brain was injured,

284
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:10,100
so some parts of his memory
might be fuzzy.

285
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:11,380
But the doctor said

286
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:14,770
he can live and learn normally,

287
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:16,820
so you could say he was fully recovered.

288
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:18,210
Right?

289
00:17:18,210 --> 00:17:18,860
Fang Muyang?

290
00:17:19,380 --> 00:17:20,180
Comrade?

291
00:17:20,690 --> 00:17:21,290
Yes.

292
00:17:22,340 --> 00:17:22,970
Yes.

293
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:26,710
Wonderful. How nice.

294
00:17:27,140 --> 00:17:28,340
Allow me to introduce

295
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:31,200
Ms. Wang from our Publicity Division.

296
00:17:31,530 --> 00:17:32,820
I got her here

297
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:35,690
to write an article about you.

298
00:17:35,830 --> 00:17:38,110
I'm going to make
everyone in the factory

299
00:17:38,340 --> 00:17:40,870
learn from your noble qualities.

300
00:17:41,180 --> 00:17:42,010
Hello, Ms. Wang.

301
00:17:42,010 --> 00:17:43,290
Hello, Fang Muyang.

302
00:17:43,290 --> 00:17:44,900
Why don't you start with

303
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:46,070
what you thought

304
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:47,250
when you were saving lives?

305
00:17:47,380 --> 00:17:47,700
Yeah.

306
00:17:47,810 --> 00:17:49,600
(Thank goodness I prepared for this.)

307
00:17:49,730 --> 00:17:50,490
Ms. Xu.

308
00:17:51,290 --> 00:17:53,110
When I was saving them,
my mind was blank.

309
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:55,130
That's because to me,
saving lives is an instinct.

310
00:17:55,130 --> 00:17:56,419
It doesn't require preparation.

311
00:17:56,420 --> 00:17:57,650
If I must think of something...

312
00:17:58,310 --> 00:17:58,880
If...

313
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,160
If I...

314
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:11,660
If what?

315
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,690
What were you thinking?

316
00:18:22,180 --> 00:18:22,820
Fei Ni.

317
00:18:24,730 --> 00:18:27,680
I thought he's fully recovered?

318
00:18:29,890 --> 00:18:30,400
He...

319
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:32,620
Maybe...

320
00:18:33,910 --> 00:18:35,100
Maybe he's nervous.

321
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:38,140
Fang Muyang.

322
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:40,660
If you must think...

323
00:18:47,010 --> 00:18:48,090
If I must think,

324
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:50,030
I want to say

325
00:18:50,770 --> 00:18:51,900
that the past few weeks

326
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,340
were the happiest time I had

327
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:57,140
since I could remember.

328
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:00,490
Fei Ni often says that I'm a hero,

329
00:19:01,026 --> 00:19:02,537
and that she should learn from me.

330
00:19:03,140 --> 00:19:03,820
But she

331
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:06,660
deserves my full admiration.

332
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:09,280
To take care of me, a stranger,

333
00:19:10,290 --> 00:19:11,900
she sacrificed her own time,

334
00:19:12,490 --> 00:19:13,970
not asking for anything in return.

335
00:19:15,826 --> 00:19:17,860
She taught me everything,
from brushing my teeth.

336
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:19,850
She was patient with me,

337
00:19:20,690 --> 00:19:21,630
and never gave up on me.

338
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:23,730
I'm lucky

339
00:19:24,620 --> 00:19:26,350
to have met her just when

340
00:19:26,350 --> 00:19:26,920
I needed help.

341
00:19:28,140 --> 00:19:29,450
She helped me stand up again

342
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:31,920
and face life.

343
00:19:33,010 --> 00:19:34,660
She is our true role model.

344
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:39,090
Today, I'm able to stand here

345
00:19:39,090 --> 00:19:40,040
healthy and well

346
00:19:41,050 --> 00:19:41,940
because of her.

347
00:19:48,580 --> 00:19:49,530
Marvelous!

348
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:51,400
Wonderful!

349
00:19:51,760 --> 00:19:52,580
A round of applause!

350
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:04,530
Wonderful.

351
00:20:04,660 --> 00:20:05,470
Fei Ni.

352
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:07,050
You did a great job!

353
00:20:07,230 --> 00:20:08,480
You have gloriously completed

354
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:10,970
a gargantuan task assigned to you!

355
00:20:11,182 --> 00:20:13,530
Tomorrow, I'll put in a good word
with the factory leaders.

356
00:20:13,537 --> 00:20:14,870
An excellent worker like you

357
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:16,010
ought to be

358
00:20:16,010 --> 00:20:16,940
a role model

359
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:18,880
and a university student!

360
00:20:20,450 --> 00:20:21,580
Thank you, Ms. Xu!

361
00:20:21,580 --> 00:20:23,450
I won't disappoint you and the factory!

362
00:20:25,180 --> 00:20:26,250
How wonderful.

363
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:33,690
Fang Muyang.

364
00:20:33,950 --> 00:20:35,680
Let's take a photo.

365
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:36,300
- Yes.
- Sure.

366
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:36,850
Come on.

367
00:20:54,004 --> 00:20:55,140
Why are you staring at me?

368
00:20:55,660 --> 00:20:58,180
Why didn't you follow my draft?

369
00:20:59,550 --> 00:21:01,190
You scared me when you said that.

370
00:21:01,530 --> 00:21:03,250
I already forgot about what you wrote.

371
00:21:04,026 --> 00:21:05,380
Besides, I didn't want to lie.

372
00:21:05,970 --> 00:21:07,420
You were still lying.

373
00:21:07,490 --> 00:21:08,450
What's with

374
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:11,730
"the happiest time you had
since you could remember"?

375
00:21:11,730 --> 00:21:12,770
That's true.

376
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:14,340
Impossible.

377
00:21:15,210 --> 00:21:16,840
As an amnesiac,

378
00:21:17,210 --> 00:21:18,400
whatever I could remember

379
00:21:18,650 --> 00:21:20,900
starts from the moment
I woke up in the hospital, right?

380
00:21:22,620 --> 00:21:23,810
Besides, I meant it

381
00:21:24,071 --> 00:21:26,093
when I said it was
the happiest time I had.

382
00:21:31,026 --> 00:21:32,050
You did a great job.

383
00:21:32,050 --> 00:21:33,210
I'll buy you an ice cream.

384
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:38,140
Dig in.

385
00:21:40,970 --> 00:21:42,660
This is real ice cream.

386
00:21:42,970 --> 00:21:43,570
Dig in.

387
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,440
But this isn't what I wanted to eat.

388
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:49,340
That's enough.

389
00:21:49,620 --> 00:21:50,450
Don't draw.

390
00:21:50,580 --> 00:21:51,970
I know what you're thinking.

391
00:21:53,050 --> 00:21:54,640
I can't afford that.

392
00:21:54,770 --> 00:21:56,270
Only the fancy restaurants sell those.

393
00:21:56,670 --> 00:21:57,730
Try this.

394
00:21:58,450 --> 00:21:59,510
It's delicious.

395
00:22:09,730 --> 00:22:10,450
Yummy, right?

396
00:22:10,690 --> 00:22:11,920
I wasn't lying.

397
00:22:12,210 --> 00:22:13,450
You know,

398
00:22:13,450 --> 00:22:15,970
in the past, the only time
my parents would buy this for me

399
00:22:15,970 --> 00:22:17,648
was when I scored first place in exams.

400
00:22:19,515 --> 00:22:20,950
Do you often score first place?

401
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,030
Not often.

402
00:22:23,450 --> 00:22:24,290
Every time.

403
00:22:25,471 --> 00:22:27,770
If university intakes are still
based on academic merit,

404
00:22:27,770 --> 00:22:29,050
I'd have secured a place.

405
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:31,590
Unlike now,
where I have to resort to tricks.

406
00:22:36,420 --> 00:22:37,690
So, you took care of me

407
00:22:39,010 --> 00:22:40,340
to go to university?

408
00:22:54,450 --> 00:22:55,580
Of course not.

409
00:22:55,790 --> 00:22:56,770
Did I say that?

410
00:22:57,450 --> 00:22:58,780
Your brain is still injured.

411
00:22:58,780 --> 00:23:00,020
Maybe you heard wrongly.

412
00:23:01,820 --> 00:23:03,290
That's what you said.

413
00:23:03,730 --> 00:23:05,690
You had to resort to tricks
to go to university.

414
00:23:06,580 --> 00:23:07,700
What I said was,

415
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:10,290
I took care of you
out of pure goodness from my heart.

416
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:14,380
So, you had an ulterior motive.

417
00:23:16,450 --> 00:23:18,590
Isn't that normal?

418
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:21,680
You needed someone to nurse you,
and I wanted to go to university.

419
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:24,160
We're just satisfying
each others' needs.

420
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:27,300
Would you say that in front of Ms. Xu?

421
00:23:28,380 --> 00:23:30,260
I wouldn't, and you can't, either.

422
00:23:30,490 --> 00:23:32,450
Now, we're on the same boat.

423
00:23:32,530 --> 00:23:33,530
Telling her

424
00:23:34,090 --> 00:23:35,140
won't do you any good.

425
00:23:36,960 --> 00:23:37,730
Not necessarily.

426
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:39,170
I'm ill.

427
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,110
If I'm in a bad mood,

428
00:23:41,110 --> 00:23:42,740
or I don't get to eat what I want,

429
00:23:43,220 --> 00:23:44,600
I might just blabber.

430
00:23:50,530 --> 00:23:51,210
Fine.

431
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:54,010
I'll buy you that thing
in your sketchbook.

432
00:23:57,290 --> 00:23:57,820
What's wrong?

433
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:06,530
I can't afford a piano!

434
00:24:06,530 --> 00:24:11,780
(Jiangcheng Vintage Store)

435
00:24:26,190 --> 00:24:26,940
Go on.

436
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:28,730
I can't remember.

437
00:24:29,970 --> 00:24:32,110
You'll remember when you play.

438
00:24:32,630 --> 00:24:34,290
Your grandma had a piano, too.

439
00:24:34,290 --> 00:24:35,648
I'm sure you know how to play.

440
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:45,270
I'll teach you.

441
00:24:50,340 --> 00:24:52,970
Your grandma donated her piano
to the school.

442
00:24:53,604 --> 00:24:55,450
That's how I learned to play the piano.

443
00:25:25,820 --> 00:25:30,540
♪In spring, I think of you♪

444
00:25:32,740 --> 00:25:37,540
♪In summer, I think of you♪

445
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:42,740
♪The fallen leaves in autumn♪

446
00:25:42,820 --> 00:25:46,300
♪You belong to me♪

447
00:25:46,700 --> 00:25:50,460
♪When the world is covered in snow♪

448
00:25:50,540 --> 00:25:55,380
♪I still think of you♪

449
00:25:57,180 --> 00:26:02,260
♪There's a small place♪

450
00:26:03,820 --> 00:26:09,740
♪Where everyone has big dreams♪

451
00:26:11,020 --> 00:26:17,900
♪Every cute face♪

452
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:24,340
♪Glows from the heart♪

453
00:26:24,580 --> 00:26:25,680
Can you remember anything?

454
00:26:27,740 --> 00:26:28,970
I can remember

455
00:26:29,970 --> 00:26:31,680
that I used to play the piano.

456
00:26:34,620 --> 00:26:35,340
What else?

457
00:26:39,260 --> 00:26:45,380
♪You belong to me, you see the light♪

458
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:45,920
Nothing.

459
00:26:48,660 --> 00:26:49,180
It's okay.

460
00:26:49,660 --> 00:26:51,140
It's a good start.

461
00:26:51,290 --> 00:26:52,290
I'm sure

462
00:26:52,420 --> 00:26:54,330
you'll remember everything soon.

463
00:26:54,390 --> 00:26:56,050
I'll make sure to get you
nutritious food.

464
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:58,150
Who knows, you'll recover tomorrow.

465
00:27:00,950 --> 00:27:01,370
Yeah.

466
00:27:02,580 --> 00:27:03,180
Let's play.

467
00:27:19,010 --> 00:27:19,620
Ms. Xu.

468
00:27:20,915 --> 00:27:23,340
Here's your speech draft
for the meeting two days later.

469
00:27:23,530 --> 00:27:24,640
Is there anything

470
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:25,630
you want me to change?

471
00:27:29,450 --> 00:27:32,210
You're getting better at writing.

472
00:27:32,426 --> 00:27:35,026
The last time I attended
a campaign meeting in the city,

473
00:27:35,182 --> 00:27:36,400
my speech was highly praised

474
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:37,890
by the city-level leaders.

475
00:27:40,140 --> 00:27:41,390
You're the one

476
00:27:41,710 --> 00:27:44,480
in this factory
who understands me the most.

477
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:46,180
Given your ability,

478
00:27:46,580 --> 00:27:47,900
writing speeches for me

479
00:27:48,182 --> 00:27:49,310
is a waste of your talent.

480
00:27:49,970 --> 00:27:51,780
No, Ms. Xu.

481
00:27:52,770 --> 00:27:54,270
You took me under your wing.

482
00:27:54,770 --> 00:27:55,970
I got to enter the university

483
00:27:56,340 --> 00:27:57,500
because you recommended me.

484
00:27:58,090 --> 00:27:59,330
I'm just doing my part.

485
00:27:59,580 --> 00:28:00,380
Besides,

486
00:28:00,770 --> 00:28:02,770
nothing else helps me improve faster

487
00:28:02,770 --> 00:28:03,900
than learning from you.

488
00:28:06,290 --> 00:28:07,010
Ms. Xu.

489
00:28:07,580 --> 00:28:09,450
The Publicity Board has been updated.

490
00:28:10,510 --> 00:28:11,210
Got it.

491
00:28:13,380 --> 00:28:14,080
Let's see it.

492
00:28:22,380 --> 00:28:23,100
Feng.

493
00:28:24,020 --> 00:28:26,260
What do you think of this edition?

494
00:28:30,493 --> 00:28:31,280
It looks energetic.

495
00:28:31,580 --> 00:28:32,580
It's also neat

496
00:28:32,582 --> 00:28:33,730
and beautifully written.

497
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:35,239
The new university graduates recruited

498
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:37,110
by Publicity Division
this time are impressive.

499
00:28:41,620 --> 00:28:42,140
Ms. Xu.

500
00:28:43,970 --> 00:28:46,560
Are you really going to recommend
Fei Ni for the university slot?

501
00:28:48,970 --> 00:28:49,520
What's wrong?

502
00:28:50,420 --> 00:28:51,790
You think she's not good enough?

503
00:28:52,640 --> 00:28:53,210
No.

504
00:28:54,740 --> 00:28:55,490
I was just thinking

505
00:28:55,782 --> 00:28:57,290
that the factory has already chosen

506
00:28:57,290 --> 00:28:58,340
our candidates this year.

507
00:28:58,340 --> 00:28:59,871
Maybe she can wait till next year.

508
00:28:59,915 --> 00:29:00,537
Perfect timing.

509
00:29:00,770 --> 00:29:01,810
I was about to ask

510
00:29:02,250 --> 00:29:03,820
for your opinion on this matter.

511
00:29:04,770 --> 00:29:05,910
I was planning

512
00:29:06,420 --> 00:29:09,520
to let Wang Defa
join next year's intake.

513
00:29:10,080 --> 00:29:13,650
After all, he was chosen
without proper consideration,

514
00:29:13,820 --> 00:29:15,170
so we ought to observe him further.

515
00:29:15,380 --> 00:29:16,800
Besides, Fei Ni

516
00:29:17,180 --> 00:29:19,070
has made a significant contribution.

517
00:29:19,248 --> 00:29:21,804
No one would question
if we bend the rules for her this time.

518
00:29:22,380 --> 00:29:23,210
But, Ms. Xu.

519
00:29:23,210 --> 00:29:24,660
- This is...
- Feng.

520
00:29:25,230 --> 00:29:27,290
Are you in a relationship

521
00:29:28,180 --> 00:29:30,050
with Wang Defa?

522
00:29:33,860 --> 00:29:35,250
It's okay to date,

523
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:38,204
but you're part of the factory's
core management team.

524
00:29:38,560 --> 00:29:40,620
If you insist on
referring him to university,

525
00:29:41,770 --> 00:29:44,180
it might cause some misunderstanding.

526
00:29:45,140 --> 00:29:46,480
That's why I'm doing this

527
00:29:46,970 --> 00:29:48,790
for your own good.

528
00:29:49,050 --> 00:29:50,940
He's going to university,

529
00:29:51,100 --> 00:29:52,290
just later.

530
00:29:52,940 --> 00:29:54,370
You don't need to rush.

531
00:29:55,450 --> 00:29:56,250
I understand.

532
00:29:57,660 --> 00:29:58,720
Thank you, Ms. Xu.

533
00:29:59,660 --> 00:30:01,280
Another reminder.

534
00:30:01,630 --> 00:30:03,240
You're not married yet.

535
00:30:03,650 --> 00:30:05,050
Be mindful of what you do.

536
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:08,170
If word of this gets out,

537
00:30:08,420 --> 00:30:09,770
people might assume

538
00:30:10,250 --> 00:30:11,750
improper things about the factory.

539
00:30:13,730 --> 00:30:14,650
Don't worry, Ms. Xu.

540
00:30:30,340 --> 00:30:39,860
(Hongxing Supply
and Marketing Cooperative)

541
00:31:00,250 --> 00:31:01,600
Here, take this.

542
00:31:02,340 --> 00:31:03,140
Lin Mei.

543
00:31:06,340 --> 00:31:07,660
You look like you have good news.

544
00:31:10,250 --> 00:31:11,190
How should I put it?

545
00:31:11,970 --> 00:31:14,290
The person standing before you

546
00:31:14,290 --> 00:31:16,590
is not the usual Fei Ni,

547
00:31:17,620 --> 00:31:21,750
but a future student of
the Worker-Peasant-Soldier University.

548
00:31:22,210 --> 00:31:23,140
Really?

549
00:31:24,310 --> 00:31:24,820
Keep it down.

550
00:31:25,530 --> 00:31:26,220
Keep it down.

551
00:31:26,580 --> 00:31:27,260
Ms. Chen.

552
00:31:27,450 --> 00:31:29,210
Mind the counter for me.
I'll be right back.

553
00:31:29,210 --> 00:31:30,490
Let's talk outside.

554
00:31:31,100 --> 00:31:32,070
Come on.

555
00:31:32,420 --> 00:31:33,180
What's the story?

556
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:34,610
Don't put your hands behind.

557
00:31:35,580 --> 00:31:36,050
Come on.

558
00:31:38,770 --> 00:31:39,210
Here.

559
00:31:41,660 --> 00:31:43,782
Your factory is letting you
go to university?

560
00:31:44,180 --> 00:31:45,360
They haven't announced it yet,

561
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:46,580
but Ms. Xu said

562
00:31:46,580 --> 00:31:47,770
my slot is guaranteed.

563
00:31:47,970 --> 00:31:49,970
I'm sure they'll announce it

564
00:31:49,970 --> 00:31:51,026
when my brother returns.

565
00:31:51,340 --> 00:31:51,820
Phooey.

566
00:31:51,820 --> 00:31:52,470
Touch wood.

567
00:31:54,730 --> 00:31:55,250
Why?

568
00:31:55,626 --> 00:31:56,820
When your brother returns,

569
00:31:57,290 --> 00:31:58,860
it'd probably be years later.

570
00:32:00,900 --> 00:32:01,840
What's wrong?

571
00:32:02,026 --> 00:32:04,137
Hasn't he submitted
his application to return?

572
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:06,240
Of course not.

573
00:32:07,450 --> 00:32:09,450
Back in autumn,
he said after the autumn harvest.

574
00:32:09,450 --> 00:32:11,620
In winter, he said
that the mountain roads are closed.

575
00:32:11,620 --> 00:32:13,110
Now that it's spring,

576
00:32:13,204 --> 00:32:14,671
he said he's planting new crops.

577
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:17,210
I don't get it.

578
00:32:17,510 --> 00:32:18,620
Is he the only worker

579
00:32:19,100 --> 00:32:20,470
in Great Northern Wilderness?

580
00:32:20,970 --> 00:32:23,180
It's not like everyone
in Great Northern Wilderness

581
00:32:23,180 --> 00:32:24,310
would starve without him.

582
00:32:25,620 --> 00:32:26,380
I think

583
00:32:26,380 --> 00:32:27,826
he's not even planning to come back.

584
00:32:28,050 --> 00:32:29,420
Impossible.

585
00:32:29,420 --> 00:32:31,040
Who wouldn't want to come home?

586
00:32:31,340 --> 00:32:32,100
I'll ask him

587
00:32:32,340 --> 00:32:33,420
the next time I call him.

588
00:32:36,140 --> 00:32:37,290
Forget it, stay out of this.

589
00:32:37,730 --> 00:32:39,110
Just focus on your plans.

590
00:32:40,180 --> 00:32:41,900
This is his only chance to return.

591
00:32:41,970 --> 00:32:43,180
I'll kidnap him if I have to.

592
00:32:43,340 --> 00:32:44,730
You don't need my help?

593
00:32:44,730 --> 00:32:45,320
No.

594
00:32:46,010 --> 00:32:47,010
I know how to handle

595
00:32:47,290 --> 00:32:48,380
your brother.

596
00:32:48,750 --> 00:32:49,260
Fine.

597
00:32:52,900 --> 00:32:54,770
Come on, I need to buy some meat.

598
00:32:55,690 --> 00:32:56,730
Someone's splurging today.

599
00:32:56,900 --> 00:32:58,570
I'm cooking for Fang Muyang.

600
00:32:59,537 --> 00:33:00,730
I think there's meat in stock.

601
00:33:00,730 --> 00:33:01,180
Come on.

602
00:33:07,010 --> 00:33:07,730
Lin Mei.

603
00:33:07,730 --> 00:33:08,450
Ms. Feng.

604
00:33:08,450 --> 00:33:09,840
Meat available
at the cooperative tomorrow?

605
00:33:09,848 --> 00:33:10,293
Yes.

606
00:33:10,380 --> 00:33:11,530
Come early tomorrow.

607
00:33:11,530 --> 00:33:12,210
Okay.

608
00:33:16,210 --> 00:33:18,300
(Mrs. Lin)
Your favorite egg soup.

609
00:33:18,710 --> 00:33:19,050
Here.

610
00:33:19,050 --> 00:33:19,760
Open your mouth.

611
00:33:20,340 --> 00:33:21,080
Yummy?

612
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,740
(Lin Jianshe)

613
00:33:22,860 --> 00:33:23,430
Mom.

614
00:33:23,430 --> 00:33:24,010
I'm back.

615
00:33:24,420 --> 00:33:25,180
You're back.

616
00:33:25,180 --> 00:33:26,010
Here, Jianshe.

617
00:33:26,010 --> 00:33:27,360
Finish this in the kitchen.

618
00:33:27,580 --> 00:33:28,420
Be careful.

619
00:33:28,420 --> 00:33:29,690
Don't spill it.

620
00:33:31,420 --> 00:33:32,730
You don't have to make him hide.

621
00:33:32,860 --> 00:33:33,530
I wouldn't

622
00:33:33,530 --> 00:33:35,200
steal food from a kid.

623
00:33:35,782 --> 00:33:37,071
Here, this month's meat coupons.

624
00:33:38,250 --> 00:33:39,050
Meat coupons?

625
00:33:39,050 --> 00:33:40,900
How many days have you been keeping it?

626
00:33:40,900 --> 00:33:41,871
Seriously.

627
00:33:51,010 --> 00:33:51,940
Go cook dinner.

628
00:33:51,940 --> 00:33:53,915
Your dad and brother
are getting off work soon.

629
00:33:54,210 --> 00:33:55,970
Aihong is working night shift,
isn't she?

630
00:33:55,970 --> 00:33:57,140
Why isn't she cooking?

631
00:33:57,140 --> 00:33:58,340
She's working night shift,

632
00:33:58,340 --> 00:33:59,770
so she needs to rest during the day,

633
00:33:59,770 --> 00:34:01,300
or else she won't have energy to work.

634
00:34:01,620 --> 00:34:03,130
I've been standing all day too.

635
00:34:03,130 --> 00:34:04,050
I'm tired as well.

636
00:34:05,250 --> 00:34:06,240
Why are you complaining?

637
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:08,010
What's wrong with doing some chores?

638
00:34:08,010 --> 00:34:08,900
Think about it.

639
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:10,010
Your sister-in-law

640
00:34:10,010 --> 00:34:12,050
let you take over her job
in the cooperative.

641
00:34:12,060 --> 00:34:14,071
That's why she's working
in the mechanical factory,

642
00:34:14,071 --> 00:34:15,300
working irregular shifts.

643
00:34:15,300 --> 00:34:16,490
How exhausting.

644
00:34:16,970 --> 00:34:18,730
She let me take over her job?

645
00:34:18,730 --> 00:34:20,604
It was your job before you retired,
so I took over.

646
00:34:20,626 --> 00:34:21,620
That's perfectly normal.

647
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:23,280
Your daughter is worth less

648
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:24,700
than your daughter-in-law now?

649
00:34:25,460 --> 00:34:27,900
Once you get married,
you won't be part of the family anymore.

650
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:30,270
Your dad and I will have to rely on
Aihong and your brother

651
00:34:30,270 --> 00:34:31,040
to take care of us.

652
00:34:31,650 --> 00:34:33,340
Be grateful.

653
00:34:33,340 --> 00:34:35,380
So many educated youths
are jobless once they return.

654
00:34:35,380 --> 00:34:37,130
They can't even afford to buy a bed.

655
00:34:37,130 --> 00:34:38,740
Why do you keep sulking

656
00:34:38,740 --> 00:34:40,450
when I ask you to do some chores?

657
00:34:43,010 --> 00:34:43,610
Mom.

658
00:34:43,700 --> 00:34:45,340
Stop lecturing Lin Mei.

659
00:34:45,570 --> 00:34:46,900
Cooking dinner, is it?

660
00:34:46,970 --> 00:34:47,740
I'll do it.

661
00:34:48,940 --> 00:34:49,650
Why you...

662
00:35:08,970 --> 00:35:10,248
I'll do it.

663
00:35:11,940 --> 00:35:13,100
If I make you work,

664
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:14,340
I'd be a sinner.

665
00:35:14,340 --> 00:35:15,900
Be nice to your sister-in-law!

666
00:35:15,970 --> 00:35:17,960
(Fang Aihong)
Is it so difficult to cook dinner?

667
00:35:18,004 --> 00:35:19,070
Ungrateful!

668
00:35:19,790 --> 00:35:21,220
Mom, don't be mad.

669
00:35:23,300 --> 00:35:24,170
What are you making?

670
00:35:25,130 --> 00:35:26,660
Making a scarf for my grandson.

671
00:35:26,660 --> 00:35:27,490
Nice color, isn't it?

672
00:35:27,490 --> 00:35:28,570
Yes, it looks pretty.

673
00:35:30,420 --> 00:35:30,860
Dinner?

674
00:35:31,570 --> 00:35:32,250
Huh?

675
00:35:35,130 --> 00:35:36,100
No dinner.

676
00:35:45,260 --> 00:35:45,970
Comrade.

677
00:35:45,970 --> 00:35:47,440
I'd like to make a long-distance call.

678
00:36:05,430 --> 00:36:05,860
Hello?

679
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:06,740
Lin Mei?

680
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,248
Have you prepared
your return application?

681
00:36:12,220 --> 00:36:12,810
Lin Mei.

682
00:36:13,990 --> 00:36:14,970
Don't be angry.

683
00:36:15,420 --> 00:36:16,090
Listen to me.

684
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:20,260
I really can't go back now.

685
00:36:23,830 --> 00:36:25,160
There's only one slot,

686
00:36:25,570 --> 00:36:27,230
and you finally stand a chance.

687
00:36:27,420 --> 00:36:29,120
If you don't submit it, it's gone.

688
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:30,450
Fei Ting.

689
00:36:31,450 --> 00:36:32,320
I'm telling you.

690
00:36:34,071 --> 00:36:37,160
I don't want to stay with
my family any longer, even for a day.

691
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,870
Come back quickly.

692
00:36:44,300 --> 00:36:45,230
Otherwise, I...

693
00:36:46,430 --> 00:36:47,120
Or else...

694
00:36:47,700 --> 00:36:48,820
Even if I go back,

695
00:36:48,820 --> 00:36:50,190
we have no place to stay.

696
00:36:52,970 --> 00:36:53,450
Lin Mei.

697
00:36:53,970 --> 00:36:55,420
You know my family.

698
00:36:55,420 --> 00:36:56,630
There are only two rooms.

699
00:36:56,900 --> 00:36:58,010
If we get married,

700
00:36:58,780 --> 00:37:00,780
we'd have to kick Ni out.

701
00:37:03,310 --> 00:37:03,700
You...

702
00:37:05,180 --> 00:37:06,780
Is this why you don't want to come back?

703
00:37:10,900 --> 00:37:12,760
Why would I kick Fei Ni out?

704
00:37:14,870 --> 00:37:15,440
But...

705
00:37:17,090 --> 00:37:18,470
But if you keep putting it off...

706
00:37:19,450 --> 00:37:19,820
I...

707
00:37:21,490 --> 00:37:22,780
What should I do?

708
00:37:24,190 --> 00:37:26,480
My parents are already
arranging blind dates for me.

709
00:37:27,940 --> 00:37:28,650
Fei Ting.

710
00:37:30,010 --> 00:37:31,450
You need to be considerate of me.

711
00:37:39,860 --> 00:37:41,010
Lin Mei, I...

712
00:37:43,290 --> 00:37:44,030
I'm sorry.

713
00:37:45,700 --> 00:37:47,280
If you can find someone better,

714
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:49,080
I...

715
00:37:51,450 --> 00:37:52,490
I wish you well.

716
00:38:22,900 --> 00:38:26,740
(Application to Return)

717
00:38:53,900 --> 00:38:57,900
(Inpatient Department)

718
00:39:13,920 --> 00:39:14,440
Wait.

719
00:39:14,626 --> 00:39:16,250
How do you know he hasn't recovered yet?

720
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:17,840
He didn't recognize me

721
00:39:17,915 --> 00:39:19,070
when he saw me in the office.

722
00:39:20,130 --> 00:39:21,220
Something's off.

723
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:26,490
Go, test him.

724
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:28,120
What if he recognizes me?

725
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:28,820
Come on.

726
00:39:29,750 --> 00:39:31,170
If he's regained his memories,

727
00:39:31,440 --> 00:39:33,200
he'd remember you anyway.

728
00:39:33,820 --> 00:39:35,370
But if he doesn't recognize you,

729
00:39:35,780 --> 00:39:37,650
it means he hasn't
recovered his memories.

730
00:39:37,990 --> 00:39:39,820
That means Fei Ni deceived Ms. Xu.

731
00:39:40,900 --> 00:39:43,220
Then, you'd still
get to go to university.

732
00:39:45,490 --> 00:39:46,860
Anyway, it's your choice.

733
00:39:46,860 --> 00:39:47,570
Whatever.

734
00:39:49,050 --> 00:39:49,740
I'll go.

735
00:40:03,380 --> 00:40:04,150
My leg.

736
00:40:05,420 --> 00:40:06,300
My leg!

737
00:40:06,530 --> 00:40:08,470
My leg has been crushed!

738
00:40:08,470 --> 00:40:09,530
- Comrade.
- My leg!

739
00:40:09,530 --> 00:40:10,610
- Help!
- Are you okay?

740
00:40:10,610 --> 00:40:13,050
- My leg has been crushed!
- Let me help you get up.

741
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:14,480
Here.

742
00:40:16,300 --> 00:40:17,010
Are you okay?

743
00:40:17,010 --> 00:40:18,220
I'm fine.

744
00:40:19,060 --> 00:40:19,820
Thank you, Comrade.

745
00:40:20,110 --> 00:40:21,260
My leg

746
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:22,340
was injured.

747
00:40:22,680 --> 00:40:23,430
It was

748
00:40:23,890 --> 00:40:24,590
crushed by

749
00:40:25,170 --> 00:40:26,190
a tree.

750
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:27,970
A tree?

751
00:40:27,970 --> 00:40:28,630
Yes.

752
00:40:29,737 --> 00:40:31,120
Want me to take you to a doctor?

753
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:33,010
No need.

754
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:35,010
It's just a trivial issue.

755
00:40:35,280 --> 00:40:36,230
Be careful, then.

756
00:40:36,750 --> 00:40:38,400
Sure, thank you.

757
00:40:38,700 --> 00:40:39,290
Thank you.

758
00:40:39,290 --> 00:40:39,820
No worries.

759
00:40:54,970 --> 00:40:56,010
He didn't recognize me.

760
00:40:56,130 --> 00:40:58,060
He looked at me as if I were a stranger.

761
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:00,200
Fei Ni.

762
00:41:00,690 --> 00:41:02,660
Let's see how you'll keep
this facade up.

763
00:41:02,700 --> 00:41:05,430
(Strict, Serious)

764
00:41:05,430 --> 00:41:06,130
What?

765
00:41:07,110 --> 00:41:09,440
Fang Muyang hasn't fully recovered?

766
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:13,050
I went to visit Fang Muyang today

767
00:41:13,340 --> 00:41:14,640
while representing the factory

768
00:41:14,670 --> 00:41:15,610
to thank the hospital.

769
00:41:16,320 --> 00:41:17,680
But Dr. Liang told me

770
00:41:17,980 --> 00:41:20,050
that he's not aware
of Fang Muyang's recovery.

771
00:41:20,337 --> 00:41:21,520
So, I investigated further.

772
00:41:21,670 --> 00:41:23,740
I talked to Fang Muyang's nurse

773
00:41:23,740 --> 00:41:25,280
and other patients who talked to him.

774
00:41:25,900 --> 00:41:27,520
Everyone said

775
00:41:27,910 --> 00:41:30,340
that Fang Muyang hasn't recovered yet.

776
00:41:33,570 --> 00:41:34,440
Feng.

777
00:41:36,060 --> 00:41:36,970
Mind you,

778
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:40,480
you're accusing the hero of lying.

779
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:42,320
Be careful.

780
00:41:46,670 --> 00:41:47,480
Do you have evidence?

781
00:41:47,780 --> 00:41:48,600
Ms. Xu.

782
00:41:48,740 --> 00:41:49,950
You know me best.

783
00:41:50,137 --> 00:41:51,220
If I didn't have evidence,

784
00:41:51,248 --> 00:41:52,550
I wouldn't make such accusations.

785
00:41:54,170 --> 00:41:54,900
Look, Ms. Xu.

786
00:41:55,115 --> 00:41:56,910
This is the hospital's diagnosis report.

787
00:41:58,000 --> 00:41:58,550
Of course,

788
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:01,004
(Diagnosis Report)
I trust Fang Muyang is a decent man.

789
00:42:01,048 --> 00:42:01,820
(Diagnosis: Amnesia caused by
external trauma, blood clot remains)

790
00:42:01,820 --> 00:42:02,700
I'm just worried

791
00:42:03,800 --> 00:42:05,137
that he's been manipulated.

792
00:42:28,080 --> 00:42:28,720
Ms. Tu.

793
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:32,320
Do you know why Ms. Xu wants to see me?

794
00:42:32,720 --> 00:42:33,550
I don't know.

795
00:42:33,720 --> 00:42:34,560
Wait here.

796
00:42:49,093 --> 00:42:49,950
Hello, Ms. Xu.

797
00:42:50,070 --> 00:42:50,410
Hello.

798
00:42:52,080 --> 00:42:53,200
Hello, Ms. Xu.

799
00:43:02,160 --> 00:43:03,940
Ms. Xu, you wanted to see me?

800
00:43:03,940 --> 00:43:04,530
Fei Ni.

801
00:43:05,260 --> 00:43:07,440
I hope you can tell me the truth.

802
00:43:08,060 --> 00:43:09,230
Has Fang Muyang

803
00:43:10,100 --> 00:43:12,260
fully recovered?

804
00:43:28,860 --> 00:43:33,340
♪After the laughter, I think of you♪

805
00:43:35,900 --> 00:43:40,620
♪After the storm, I think of you♪

806
00:43:43,140 --> 00:43:49,260
♪In the little courtyard,
there you are dancing♪

807
00:43:50,260 --> 00:43:54,820
♪That earnest you,
smiling so innocently♪

808
00:43:57,300 --> 00:44:02,060
♪In spring, I stay by your side♪

809
00:44:04,500 --> 00:44:08,860
♪When summer comes, I watch over you♪

810
00:44:11,220 --> 00:44:17,860
♪In the light of dawn, you belong to me♪

811
00:44:17,860 --> 00:44:27,460
♪At the edge of the world,
I will still hold you tight♪

812
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:34,700
♪There is a small place♪

813
00:44:34,700 --> 00:44:41,500
♪Where they carry big dreams♪

814
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:48,860
♪Every lovely face♪

815
00:44:49,740 --> 00:44:55,900
♪Shines brightly in the heart♪

816
00:44:56,700 --> 00:45:02,740
♪Even when we collide,
we hold our course♪

817
00:45:03,940 --> 00:45:09,740
♪Even when we stumble,
we keep our resolve♪

818
00:45:10,820 --> 00:45:17,100
♪My you, walking toward the distance♪

819
00:45:17,900 --> 00:45:26,140
♪Please carry our dreams
and let them soar♪

